<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - ELECTRONIC
        ENGINE CONTROLS - CUMMINS PT PACER - 1991 - WELDING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
        <title>WELDING</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To protect the PCU computer circuits before welding, it is mandatory to:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove the positive (+), 12 volt supply circuit to the fuel shutoff solenoid.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove the PCU engine block ground connector (Figure 1).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Disconnect both the Positive and Negative battery cables from the battery.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Attach the welder ground cable as close as possible to the part being welded.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Do not connect the welder ground cable to the PCU.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
